<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="379" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1679,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1788,1813]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378">Description.</emphasis>
Stolonal colony growing on gastropod shell. Hydrorhiza consisting of a mesh of anastomosing tubes of perisarc, not covered by a coenosarc layer. With gastrozooids and gonophores. Neither spines nor dactylozooids. Gastrozooids relatively large (
<figureCitation box="[687,760,1860,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,309,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,301,1876]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Perarella clavata (Jäderholm, 1905): A, polyp showing basal cup of perisarc (arrow); B, distal part of polyp; C, female gonophore showing basal cup of perisarc (arrow). Scale bar: 500 µm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236737/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="378">
Fig. 
<number box="[746,760,1860,1885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A) [
<quantity box="[810,913,1860,1885]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1044,1201,1860,1884]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="0.65" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.3">0.3 to 1 mm</quantity>
wide, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaderholm" box="[151,362,1895,1920]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" refString="Jaderholm, E. (1905) Hydroiden aus antarktischen und subantarktischen Meeren, gesammelt von der schwedischen Sudpolarexpedition. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Schwedischen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903, 5 (8), 1 - 41, pls. 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1905">
Jäderholm (
<number box="[292,354,1895,1920]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" value="1905.0">1905</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
], with conical hypostome and a distal crown of 
<number box="[974,1043,1895,1920]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17</number>
filiform tentacles (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1358,1895,1920]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,309,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,301,1876]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Perarella clavata (Jäderholm, 1905): A, polyp showing basal cup of perisarc (arrow); B, distal part of polyp; C, female gonophore showing basal cup of perisarc (arrow). Scale bar: 500 µm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236737/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="378">
Fig. 
<number box="[1344,1358,1895,1920]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Gonozooids absent; gonophores directly arising from hydrorhiza, club-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1139,1932,1957]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,309,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,301,1876]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Perarella clavata (Jäderholm, 1905): A, polyp showing basal cup of perisarc (arrow); B, distal part of polyp; C, female gonophore showing basal cup of perisarc (arrow). Scale bar: 500 µm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236737/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="378">
Fig. 
<number box="[1124,1139,1932,1957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
C), about 
<quantity box="[1257,1325,1932,1956]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[151,316,1968,1993]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="0.625" valueMax="0.75" valueMin="0.5">0.50–0.75 mm</quantity>
wide. Both gastrozooids and gonophores with a short, basal cup of perisarc (
